HEADWORD: Tragi-comical
<hw>Trag`i-com"ic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>tragi-comique</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to tragi-comedy;
partaking of grave and comic scenes.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Trag`-com"ic*al*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Julian felt toward him that <qex>tragi-comic</qex> sensation which
makes us pity the object which excites it not the less that we are
somewhat inclined to laugh amid our sympathy.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W.
Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tragi-comi-pastoral</ent>⟦br⟧
